The paper discusses the problem of evolving NoSQL databases, which is a common issue in database systems and falls under the category of database management systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a solution to this problem using an extension to Redis, which is a popular data structure server and falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the practical implications of the proposed solution, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the proposed solution on high-availability applications, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
